## All In One line

A `for` loop packages those exact three things into a single, neat pair of parentheses, separated by semicolons `;`.

```java
for (start; condition; update) {
  // Code
}
```

It is the absolute best way to repeat code exactly X number of times.

slides.codeSnippet:
class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println("Starting...");

    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
      System.out.println("Loop iteration: " + i);
    }

    System.out.println("Done looping!");
  }
}

class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println("Liftoff Sequence Initiated...");

    // Start at 3, run as long as i > 0, subtract 1 each time
    for (int i = 3; i > 0; i--) {
      System.out.println(i + "...");
    }

    System.out.println("🚀 Liftoff!");
  }
}
